1
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:09,906
Had a little girl’s bed made of pine

2
00:00:10,056 --> 00:00:14,961
Slide on the side and a ladder to climb

3
00:00:15,111 --> 00:00:20,017
Underneath was a temple space

4
00:00:20,167 --> 00:00:25,073
Where I’d sit for hours in a quiet place

5
00:00:25,223 --> 00:00:30,129
One day I stood there, legs too long

6
00:00:30,279 --> 00:00:35,184
The steps felt short, the fit felt wrong

7
00:00:35,334 --> 00:00:40,240
Stopped climbing up, just stayed below

8
00:00:40,390 --> 00:00:45,296
Then took to the couch like it was my own

9
00:00:45,446 --> 00:00:50,352
Crashed in the middle of the downstairs
floor

10
00:00:50,502 --> 00:00:55,407
Blankets piled, shoes by the door

11
00:00:55,557 --> 00:01:00,463
Everyone stepping around my spot

12
00:01:00,613 --> 00:01:05,519
They did complain — but not a lot

13
00:01:05,669 --> 00:01:10,575
Some things change without much plan

14
00:01:10,725 --> 00:01:15,630
You don’t outgrow — you just expand

15
00:01:15,780 --> 00:01:20,686
It looks like a sofa, but it’s a bed they
say

16
00:01:20,836 --> 00:01:25,742
With a trundle drawer for friends to stay

17
00:01:25,892 --> 00:01:30,798
Dad took weeks to list but sold real fast

18
00:01:30,948 --> 00:01:35,853
We hauled it out the door and the memories
passed

19
00:01:36,004 --> 00:01:40,909
A lady pulled up the driveway with care

20
00:01:41,059 --> 00:01:45,965
And the slide went rolling through the air

21
00:01:46,115 --> 00:01:51,021
By then I’d claimed the couch as mine

22
00:01:51,171 --> 00:01:56,076
Back was sore but I said I was fine

23
00:01:56,226 --> 00:02:01,132
Mom said, “Let’s fix this couch-bed thing”

24
00:02:01,282 --> 00:02:06,188
Found me a frame with a curving wing

25
00:02:06,338 --> 00:02:11,244
Some things change without much plan

26
00:02:11,394 --> 00:02:16,299
You don’t outgrow — you just expand

27
00:02:16,450 --> 00:02:21,355
It looks like a sofa, but it’s a bed they
say

28
00:02:21,505 --> 00:02:26,411
With a trundle drawer for friends to stay

29
00:02:26,561 --> 00:02:31,467
Got some throw pillows, velvet and bright

30
00:02:31,617 --> 00:02:36,522
With beads and tassels and gold stitched
light

31
00:02:36,672 --> 00:02:41,578
They’re kind of a lot — a little too much

32
00:02:41,728 --> 00:02:46,634
But I love how they sparkle when I touch

33
00:02:46,784 --> 00:02:51,690
Some things change without much sound

34
00:02:51,840 --> 00:02:56,745
Just a slide bed gone and a new one found

35
00:02:56,895 --> 00:03:01,801
It looks like a sofa, but it’s a bed they
say

36
00:03:01,951 --> 00:03:06,857
With a trundle drawer for friends to stay
